			<B><TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="12" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">The report on this bar chart is jumbled up. Look carefully at the chart and drag down the paragraph descriptions (Introduction, Development, Conclusion) to the appropriate sentences.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT></B>
		</header>
				<section id="body">
				<textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[1]<font color="#000000">: This pattern is true for almost all other equipment.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[2]<font color="#000000">: For example, the percentage of boys with computers in their bedroom is almost twice the percentage for girls.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[3]<font color="#000000">: Almost 1 in 2 children have one.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[4]<font color="#000000">: It is clear that a large proportion of all children, just over 50 per cent, have some kind of equipment in their bedroom and that the percentage is considerably higher for boys.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[5]<font color="#000000">: The television is closely followed by games consoles in popularity.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[6]<font color="#000000">: The only exception is video cassette recorders, which are slightly more common in girls' bedrooms.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[7]<font color="#000000">: A third of boys own such consoles compared to only a fifth of girls.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[8]<font color="#000000">: A closer look at the figures shows that the most common appliance found in children's bedrooms is the television set.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[9]<font color="#000000">: However, these are far more popular with boys than with girls.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[10]: The bar chart shows the percentages of girls and boys with home entertainment equipment in their bedrooms.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[11]<font color="#000000">: We might also wonder what effect this has on their social development.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[12]: We could infer from these figures that children today spend a lot of their free time in their bedrooms.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></p></textformat><p align="left"><font size="2"></font></p><img class="leftFloat" src="../Media/Unit01_Write_e6.jpg" height="" width="" mode="1" id="1003"  /><media class="leftFloat" src="../Media/" height="" width="" mode="1" id="2001"  />
